race.comment: TERESITA (5) was safely held in tougher company last start after drifting back at this track, but prior to that won by 2.5 lengths at Q Parklands (29.81) beating Savanna Beach in a Grade 4/5 on September 25. Has a very good strike-rate from this draw, with three wins from five starts. Ready to return to form. ROBERT KEEPING (1) hit the ground running from out wide with a fast early sectional but run over late and missed the frame when a 2.75 lengths fourth (29.77) over 520m at this track. Unbeaten from this box in three starts. Should be about the money. SCREAMING VIOLET (2) ran below her best last time finishing fourth (29.90) over 520m at this track in a NG. Solid record at the distance winning seven races. One of the better chances. Something for the Multiples: OZZIE NICK (4)
